This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of Natural Language Processing (cs.CL) as it proposes a semantic parser that can interact with end-users via natural language. It also involves constructing utterance-logical form pairs, which is a common task in NLP. Additionally, the paper may also belong to the sub-categories of Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) and Machine Learning (cs.LG) as it involves learning a general strategy for parsing unseen utterances. The paper may also be relevant to the sub-categories of Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) and Information Retrieval (cs.IR) as these fields often involve natural language processing and machine learning techniques.
